Body: Kurecoin is a financial solution from Africa and this vision was born by a vision team that sees the gap in the financial services sector in Africa and as a result it is found to be compatible with the information of blockchain technology, entrepreneurs. In this way, individuals can have a better and easier life.  The Kurecoin Hub is a crypto currency and fiat platform that allows you to buy, sell and store up to five crypto-currency for African users. Platform users can take unsecured loans in price as long as the assets are stored on the platform. In addition, keeping the crypto money on the platform will also make a periodic contribution to the user.  The vision behind Kure Exchange is that it is possible to host many currencies around the world. According to research, Nigeria is transferring $ 5,000,000 liquidity to the crypto money market. With the opening of the Kure exchange, investments are expected to increase visibly from both Africa and the rest of the world.  Kure Pay is a trifecta payment system solution based on block chain technology. There is one e-wallet, one payment gate and one debit / credit card in it. E purses, as well as local funds, debt / credit, crypto coins and selected global e-wallets can be used in a convenient way.  The team is built around experts in areas such as Software development, Finance, or Law, and shows that they have experience in all areas needed to be successful. They want to be seen as "Ethereum of Africa" but their teams are not entirely African, they could expand the software development space a little bit, but their squad seems to have enough potential.
